<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 21 at 1:10PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Randall
and southwestern Potter Counties through 145 PM CDT...
At 110 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Mescalero Park, or 8 miles southwest of Amarillo,
moving north at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Mescalero Park and Bushland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
